messages.text: Charlie we have a bug problem
Not sure how to explain, never seen this kind of bug
Love you. Be home in a few days.
He wouldn't come into the house
I opened the door for him and a few of the bugs escaped.
He took one look at them then got in his van and drove off without saying a word
They're everywhere. In the fridge, in our food, everywhere
Hang in there. We will deal with this properly when I get home.
Was taking a shower and I saw a bug
Don't be scared you probably just tracked it in somehow. Did you catch it?
I stepped on it with my bare feet. It was so disgusting
Just relax and get some sleep it's gone now
Saw another bug. fell asleep and woke up when I felt it in my sheets
Oh god did you kill it
Call the front desk. Maybe it's not just our house. Maybe the whole town is having an issue.
Just did. They said they haven't been having any problems. The manager checked a different room for the bugs.
It's clear. They are going to move me free of charge
Good. Move rooms and get some rest
Honey it's late. I have meetings in the morning. What is it?
One of the bugs was in my mouth. Woke me up
Killed it but then opened my mouth again and there was another
I am afraid if I open my mouth to talk another will go in somehow
I'm going to try to sleep. I'm so tired. I don't know what else to do
Okay. Just think good thoughts. This will go away soon.
I've kept my mouth shut. But there are still bugs getting in.
Charlie they're not coming from the room
I think the bugs are coming from inside of me.
Diane, listen to what you’re saying.
At least I won’t be alone there
They took an x Ray. They said nothing is wrong with me
I feel better. Going to sleep for the night. things seem to be OK
You have to be joking what's happening
I found about ten of them in my bed. In my pillow case
Nobody in the rooms, nobody at reception. No janitors. Nobody. Anywhere
I'm scared. Something bad is going to happen
Call the police? I don't know what to do
I found a scalpel. For protection.
Go outside, get out of there. Ask the first person you see for help
This is so strange. No cars anywhere
There are no lights on in any of the windows
I just threw up about 50 of them. Onto the street.
God help us I’m calling the police
Charlie they're coming from inside of me.
No they're not just wait there help is coming
I need to get them out of me
Diane take that scalpel and throw it into a sewer I don't want you to do anything stupid
It's okay. I made a cut in my stomach. Peeled back the flesh.
They are coming out of me now. By the hundreds. In a swarm.
Police are coming now. Just stay awake
There is nothing left. My body is jelly.
I am going to shrivel up. I can tell there is nothing inside of me now
The police should be here by now. Can you see them??
Charlie the bugs are swarming them. The streets are lined with them now
I am too weak to type now. All that was inside of me is now gone.
Now I know. Now I know what I am made of.
